# Comments and documentation

## Comments

- Do **not** over-comment; keep density consistent with the file.
- Add comments only when the code **does not** explain **why** (not what) something is done.
- Comments must refer to the **codebase only**—not the chat session or external narrative.

## Function documentation

- For languages that support docs: add documentation a caller would need (behavior, args, errors) when the **name and parameters are not enough** on their own.
- Skip docs when the signature already fully explains the function.
